A few nights ago I was talking to a friend of mine and just happened to mention how much I enjoy explosions and puzzle games, and wondered why there werenÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢t more games to mix these two totally different elements into a nice portable package. Well, just my luck ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â‚¬Å“ someone else had the same thought and has just released Demolition Master 3D, a game that actually bases a puzzle game around construction site explosions.
Your task in each level is to knock down different structures by placing bombs on them. You choose the types and placement of the bombs, adjust their timing if you wish (to help create a domino effect) then hit the trigger to set it off. You pass the level if you get the height of the structure knocked down to a certain target and can get bonus points if you hit items placed around the level.
