YouÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢re given a variety of different bombs to work with that have different effects on the various materials found in the game. For instance, some are good for wood and concrete but wonÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢t do much damage to steel. They also have varying blast radii and some even cause materials around them to get pulled towards the explosion rather than away from it. All in service of not just blowing up parts of the structure, but getting the whole thing to come crashing down.
But itÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s not just getting it to come down. There are certain areas youÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢ll need to avoid getting debris and other area that will give you bonuses if some does fall there. Each level has different objectives, and you can earn up to 3 stars for meeting them each time. YouÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢ll be scored on how well you do and there are various trophies and achievements that can be unlocked in the process.
WhatÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s amazing is how difficult that can actually be. Sure in first few levels itÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s easy to find the keystones of the structures and just put the bomb there, but before long it really ramps up in difficulty. ItÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s only a few missions into the 70 included where that simple strategy falls away and you need to get a lot more creative and cunning in your bombing choices.
For a game about blowing stuff up itÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s actually quite a complex endeavour. This isnÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢t the kind of thing where you just put a big stick of dynamite in the center and everything just goes flying. These are tactical, directed explosions, and if you want to knock down a structure then you need to be very exact in your placement and timing.
My only complaint about the game is probably going to sounds like a childish one, but I wish the explosions were bigger. Like, a lot bigger. In a game world where size, scope and real world value donÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢t apply, why are we blowing up 2X4ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s when we could be doing it to huge structures? ThereÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s a lot more fun in knocking down an empty building that toppling a 4 foot barrel. At the very least IÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢d like the explosions that are in the game to feel more forceful. Sticks of dynamite should feel like something when they go boom, but these just go... pop.
